headline: Delta, United allegedly selling ‘window’ seats that don’t have a view
summary: Anyone who has flown on a U.S. airline recently knows that booking the route is just the first step. Once you choose your flights, you then have to decide: Pay for a checked bag or a carry on? Book a preferred seat in an exit row or an aisle? Add the fee for early boarding? headline: Delta and Siemens to Complement their Power Solutions to Help Customers Cut Data Center Deployment Time, Costs, and Carbon Emissions
summary: Delta, a global leader in power management and smart green solutions, and Siemens Smart Infrastructure have formalized a global partnership to deliver prefabricated, modular power solutions designed to accelerate the deployment of data center infrastructure, while significantly reducing CAPEX.
